node.text:
With Leah Wyer SVP/GM of @byrdie and Founder/ Partner  of @sblabeauty, @randishinder, and me.
I promised I would put up our #instagramlive conversation but as It was a stormy day we lost our connection ( and probably a lot of you 😉) several times so I will post the snippets we were able to salvage . And @sandylinter this one includes a shout out to legendary you. So in case you were #wand-ering …here’s a bit about #sblawands and what the silver neck chin and jawline #wand can do for you! And thank you again @leahwyar for gracing us with your presence you are pure delight! #selfcaresunday 💜💛

See I told you, things are looking up!

node.text:
Happy 100th Birthday @iris.apfel 
100  years of eye catching style…through big round glasses of course‼️ 
100 years ago this Legend was born , so I thought I would look back to see what the world was like that produced such an Icon.  It was the 1920’s, the period we portray in @chicagomusical In photo # 2. Iris came to my opening night and naturally she stole the show‼️ The year Iris was born Jazz and dance clubs were all the rage, and the world was just emerging from a pandemic, known as the Spanish Flu.  Hats and gloves were de rigueur, alcohol was prohibited, and women finally won the right to vote that year‼️Iris and the automobile industry were both born in the same year‼️
And  for 100 years Iris has been taking it all in, and seeing the world through her lens has endlessly influenced and fascinated the world‼️
 I think her vitality and youth comes from her endless fascination with life.. the other day I told Iris I was going to call her back later and she said , “you can always call me anytime except tonight I’m going to bed early because I was up all night last night shooting a music video with a rapper.” That’s Iris at 100‼️Gurl, we all hope to be like you when we grow up, .. young at heart forever‼️And we ALL love you very much✨I can’t wait to celebrate with you‼️❤️🎉

node.text:
Too many are weeping tonight, too much loss, too much pain and suffering , too many families in turmoil,  too much anger hate weapons and violence. 
For a species capable of so much beauty compassion and love, humans sure have made a mess of this world. 
And we constantly hand that mess over to our troops to clean up. 
I’e met with troops several times over the years to thank them for their service in Kosovo, Macedonia, Sarajevo, USS Bataan and more…And I was often struck by how young and polite they were, how eager and sincere was their desire to be of service , to help .. it hurts to think about them tonight knowing how many  deaths and casualties there were today in Kabul  where they were helping and how close to coming home they were…
And I’ve also gone to refugee camps and it’s excruciating to think how close so many who helped our troops were to escaping the oppression of the Taliban and all the chaos they’ve endured for some 20 years. Just tragic. 
I m adding my Heartfelt condolences and sympathy for all loss and their families. 💔 
photo by Getty Image second photo yahoo news Canada

node.text:
“Call it …” time for a #tbt ‼️I’m guessing this was late 70’s or early 80’s Clairol Shampoo.it’s definitely Winter because my hair would turn darker without the sun and lighten up in the Summer..I had tricks to make that happen faster like camomille  oil from the health food store i used the oil on strands around my face. I would sip a little and pour most of the camomile tea with lemon on my hair as I sat in the sun.Never substitute the lemon with lime! Lime can cause a terrible rash when it gets on your skin in the sun! Anyway ..Hair you go, a little throwback for this beautiful Summer day! #hair #hairstyle  #haircolor @clairol_pro #haircolortips @sblabeauty 
PS Pretty cheeky

It was exciting at the beach this afternoon! The ocean was bubbling with life…Atlantic Menhaden or Moss-bunker to be precise. Menhaden is rich in Omega-3 fatty acids which are great for reducing inflammation and lowering the risk for heart disease. They were practically jumping out of the ocean right onto our plate but they’re not really good eating… oily and bony they are better in supplement form. The Bunker were chasing tiny fish that looked and sounded like giant raindrops ..and bigger fish could be seen occasionally trying to get them! 
It’s wonderful to see our ocean so alive! Sound up to swipe 🌊🐟🐟

node.text:
Meet Pat DeRosa The 100 year old holder of the 
#guinessworldrecord for the oldest professional sax player in the world. Swipe to hear him swing at last nights “Every Tuesday Weekly Free Concert” at the American Legion in charming beautiful 
#sagharbor That’s Pat’s beautiful granddaughter with @alexarayjoel . The sweetness of a small town on a hot Summer night! 🎷🎶🎵
(Speaking of swingin’ jazz check out @chicagomusical in my stories and get your tickets now!) #musickeepsyouyoung
